com.alexgilleran.icesoap.request

Interface RequestFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RequestFactoryImpl

    public interface RequestFactory
    Creates Requests, passing them a default, Apache HTTP Client based SOAPRequester implementation.
    Author:
    Alex Gilleran

    • Method Detail

      • buildRequest

        <ReturnType> SOAP11Request<ReturnType> buildRequest(String url,
                                                  SOAPEnvelope soapEnvelope,
                                                  String soapAction,
                                                  Class<ReturnType> resultClass)
        Builds a default SOAP11Request that will parse a default SOAP11Fault Fault in the event of HTTP Error 500.
        Type Parameters:
        ReturnType - The type of the object that will be returned by this request when executed (if successful).
        Parameters:
        url - The url to POST the request to.
        soapEnvelope - The SOAPEnvelope to post.
        soapAction - The SOAP action to use. Can be set to null as some SOAP services use this and some don't.
        resultClass - The class for of the return type.
        Returns:
        A request with the passed parameters, ready to have observers registered and be executed.
        See Also:
        buildRequest(String, SOAPEnvelope, String, Class, Class)

      • buildRequest

        <ReturnType,SOAPFaultType> Request<ReturnType,SOAPFaultType> buildRequest(String url,
                                                                        SOAPEnvelope soapEnvelope,
                                                                        String soapAction,
                                                                        Class<ReturnType> resultClass,
                                                                        Class<SOAPFaultType> soapFaultClass)
        Builds a new Request for a non-list return type. Use this kind of request when you want only one returned object, and want to specify a specific SOAPFault type.
        Type Parameters:
        ReturnType - The type of the object that will be returned by this request when executed (if successful)
        Parameters:
        url - The url to POST the request to
        soapEnvelope - The SOAPEnvelope to post
        soapAction - The SOAP action to use. Can be set to null as some SOAP services use this and some don't.
        resultClass - The class for of the return type.
        soapFaultClass - The class to use to parse the soap fault that will be returned from the server in the event of an HTTP 500 error.
        Returns:
        A request with the passed parameters, ready to have observers registered and be executed.

      • buildListRequest

        <ReturnType> SOAP11ListRequest<ReturnType> buildListRequest(String url,
                                                          SOAPEnvelope soapEnvelope,
                                                          String soapAction,
                                                          Class<ReturnType> resultClass)
        Creates a ListRequest that will parse a default SOAP11Fault if an HTTP 500 error is encountered. Use this sort of request when you want to get a list of the same object back from the service, and you only want basic details back if there's an error.
        Type Parameters:
        ReturnType - The type of the objects inside the list that will be returned by this request when executed (if successful).
        Parameters:
        url - The url to POST the request to.
        soapEnvelope - The SOAPEnvelope to post.
        soapAction - The SOAP action to use. Can be set to null as some SOAP services use this and some don't.
        resultClass - The class to go inside the list (e.g. List<ReturnType> ) for of the return type.
        Returns:
        A request with the passed parameters, ready to have observers registered and be executed.

      • buildListRequest

        <ReturnType,SOAPFaultType> ListRequest<ReturnType,SOAPFaultType> buildListRequest(String url,
                                                                                SOAPEnvelope soapEnvelope,
                                                                                String soapAction,
                                                                                Class<ReturnType> resultClass,
                                                                                Class<SOAPFaultType> soapFaultClass)
        Builds a ListRequest with the passed parameters. Use this sort of request when you want to get a list of the same object back from the service, and you want to specify a certain class to parse in the event of an exception.
        Type Parameters:
        ReturnType - The type of the objects inside the list that will be returned by this request when executed (if successful).
        Parameters:
        url - The url to POST the request to.
        soapEnvelope - The SOAPEnvelope to post.
        soapAction - The SOAP action to use. Can be set to null as some SOAP services use this and some don't.
        resultClass - The class to go inside the list (e.g. List<ReturnType> ) for of the return type.
        soapFaultClass - The class to use to parse the soap fault that will be returned from the server in the event of an HTTP 500 error.
        Returns:
        A request with the passed parameters, ready to have observers registered and be executed.
